LSTM

Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks are a type of recurrent neural network capable of learning order dependence in sequence prediction problems. Univariate LSTM Models. LSTMs can be used to model univariate time series forecasting problems. These are problems comprised of a single series of observations and a model is required to learn from the series of past observations to predict the next value in the sequence.
